    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-10T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6111/1061a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-10T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 10, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1207. Following for Litvinov from Joseph E. Davies:<note n="30" xml:id="d654fn30"
                        >Mr. Davies had been the American Ambassador in the Soviet Union during part
                        of the years 1937 and 1938.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“None among your many friends found more satisfaction in your appointment
                            to Washington than did we. We have found the greatest admiration and
                            pride in the extraordinary effectiveness and magnificent heroism which
                            the Soviet Union is displaying every day in this decisive battle for the
                            preservation of civilization and freedom. Please give regards to Premier
                            Stalin, Prime Minister Molotov, Ambassador Oumansky, Troyanovsky<note
                                n="31" xml:id="d654fn31">Alexander Antonovich Troyanovsky had been
                                the Ambassador of the Soviet Union to the United States from early
                                1934 until 1939.</note> and our other friends. A warm welcome will
                            be awaiting you here.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
